So we need $\sum_{j \in S} (c(j)+1) = \frac{1}{2} \sum_{j \in \text{Fin}(4n)} (c(j)+1)$

Let's compute the total sum: $\sum_{j \in \text{Fin}(4n)} (c(j)+1) = \sum_{j \in \text{Fin}(4n)} c(j) + \sum_{j \in \text{Fin}(4n)} 1 = \sum_{j \in \text{Fin}(4n)} c(j) + 4n$

